<statement>
<p>What is the solution to <m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{7}={2}{x}+{17}</m>? <input type="text" style="width:4.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/> Â  </p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>2</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{7}={2}{x}+{17}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{7}-{17}={2}{x}+{17}-{17}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}-{10}={2}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}-{10}-{7}{x}={2}{x}-{7}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{10}=-{5}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{10}}{{-{{5}}}}=\frac{{-{5}{x}}}{{-{{5}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}={x}</m>.</p>

</solution>
